Sentencas: Developing low temperature solid oxide fuel cells has been a prerequisite for commercialization.
Titulo: Structural remodeling of Ni-based anodes for solid oxide fuel cells via static magnetic field

Sentencas: In response to this issue, a novel strategy for the directional construction of Ni/SDC anodes via magnetic field to achieve better polarization than the traditional Ni/SDC anodes in low operating temperature range (<= 600 degrees C) is exploited.
Titulo: Structural remodeling of Ni-based anodes for solid oxide fuel cells via static magnetic field

Sentencas: In the condition of Ni and SDC particles lining up end to end to construct Ni/SDC anodes (Ni/SDC-B-T), the polarization resistance (R-p) of the remodeled Ni/SDC-B-T in humidified H-2 are 0.263, 0.088 and 0.037 Omega cm(2) at 500, 550 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Structural remodeling of Ni-based anodes for solid oxide fuel cells via static magnetic field

Sentencas: Furthermore, the optimization mechanism is proposed via the microstructure model.
Titulo: Structural remodeling of Ni-based anodes for solid oxide fuel cells via static magnetic field
